Analyze Your Data

Disparate Impact Alert
Indicates that there is a significant discrepancy in the way different classes are being treated, which can signal bias.

Investigate the variable further to determine whether it's reflecting discriminatory practices. Consider removing any biased variables from your story to remove their influence and to produce more ethical and accountable insights and models. 

Einstein Discovery raises this data alert when, for a sensitive variable, the selection data for one group is less than 80% of the group with the highest selection rate. The detection methodology uses an 80% threshold as the widely used standard for detecting disparate impact.
